resources.resource_name: Child mortality Indicators for State of Palestine
resources.description:
*Child mortality:*
[Number of under-five deaths](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/number-of-under-five-deaths), [Number of infant deaths](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/number-of-infant-deaths), [Number of neonatal deaths](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/number-of-neonatal-deaths), [Number of deaths among children ages 5 to 9 years](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/number-of-deaths-among-children-ages-5-to-9-years), [Number of deaths among adolescents (10 to 19 years of age)](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/number-of-deaths-among-adolescents-10-19-years-of-age), [Infant mortality rate (probability of dying between birth and age 1 per 1000 live births)](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/infant-mortality-rate-%28probability-of-dying-between-birth-and-age-1-per-1000-live-births%29), [Under-five mortality rate (probability of dying by age 5 per 1000 live births)](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/under-five-mortality-rate-%28probability-of-dying-by-age-5-per-1000-live-births%29), [Adolescent mortality rate (per 1 000 age specific cohort)](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/adolescent-mortality-rate-per-100-000-population), [Number of deaths](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/number-of-deaths), [Deaths per 1 000 live births](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/deaths-per-1-000-live-births), [Distribution of causes of death among children aged < 5 years (%)](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/distribution-of-causes-of-death-among-children-aged-5-years-%28-%29), [Neonatal mortality rate (per 1000 live births)](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/neonatal-mortality-rate-%28per-1000-live-births%29), [Stillbirth rate (per 1000 total births)](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/stillbirth-rate-%28per-1000-total-births%29), [Mortality rate among children ages 5 to 9 years (per 1000 children aged 5)](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/mortality-rate-among-children-ages-5-to-9-years-%28per-1000-children-aged-5%29)

resources.description:
*Global Health Estimates: Life expectancy and leading causes of death and disability:*
[Mortality rate for 5-14 year-olds (probability of dying per 1000 children aged 5-14 years)](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/mortality-rate-for-5-14-year-olds-%28probability-of-dying-per-1000-children-aged-5-14-years%29), [Number of under-five deaths](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/number-of-under-five-deaths), [Number of infant deaths](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/number-of-infant-deaths), [Number of neonatal deaths](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/number-of-neonatal-deaths), [Number of deaths among children ages 5 to 9 years](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/number-of-deaths-among-children-ages-5-to-9-years), [Number of deaths among adolescents (10 to 19 years of age)](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/number-of-deaths-among-adolescents-10-19-years-of-age), [nMx - age-specific death rate between ages x and x+n](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/gho-ghe-life-tables-nmx-age-specific-death-rate-between-ages-x-and-x-plus-n), [nqx - probability of dying between ages x and x+n](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/gho-ghe-life-tables-nqx-probability-of-dying-between-ages-x-and-x-n), [lx - number of people left alive at age x](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/gho-ghe-life-tables-by-who-region-global-health-estimates), [ndx - number of people dying between ages x and x+n](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/gho-ghe-life-tables-by-who-region-global-health-estimates), [nLx - person-years lived between ages x and x+n](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/gho-ghe-life-tables-nlx-person-years-lived-between-ages-x-and-x-plus-n), [Tx - person-years lived above age x](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/gho-ghe-life-tables-by-who-region-global-health-estimates), [ex - expectation of life at age x](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/gho-ghe-life-tables-by-country), [Infant mortality rate (probability of dying between birth and age 1 per 1000 live births)](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/infant-mortality-rate-%28probability-of-dying-between-birth-and-age-1-per-1000-live-births%29), [Under-five mortality rate (probability of dying by age 5 per 1000 live births)](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/under-five-mortality-rate-%28probability-of-dying-by-age-5-per-1000-live-births%29), [Age-standardized suicide rates (per 100 000 population)](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/age-standardized-suicide-rates-%28per-100-000-population%29), [Adolescent mortality rate (per 1 000 age specific cohort)](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/adolescent-mortality-rate-per-100-000-population), [Number of deaths](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/number-of-deaths), [Deaths per 1 000 live births](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/deaths-per-1-000-live-births), [Distribution of causes of death among children aged < 5 years (%)](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/distribution-of-causes-of-death-among-children-aged-5-years-%28-%29), [Number of maternal deaths](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/number-of-maternal-deaths), [Probability (%) of dying between age 30 and exact age 70 from any of cardiovascular disease, cancer, diabetes, or chronic respiratory disease](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/probability-of-dying-between-exact-ages-30-and-70-from-any-of-cardiovascular-disease-cancer-diabetes-or-chronic-respiratory-%28-%29), [Total NCD Deaths (in thousands)](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/gho-ghe-ncd-deaths-in-thousands), [Premature deaths due to noncommunicable diseases (NCD) as a proportion of all NCD deaths](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/ncd-deaths-under-age-70-%28percent-of-all-ncd-deaths%29), [Estimated number of road traffic deaths](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/estimated-number-of-road-traffic-deaths), [Estimated road traffic death rate (per 100 000 population)](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/estimated-road-traffic-death-rate-%28per-100-000-population%29), [Mortality rate attributed to unintentional poisoning (per 100 000 population)](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/mortality-rate-attributed-to-unintentional-poisoning-%28per-100-000-population%29), [Crude suicide rates (per 100 000 population)](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/crude-suicide-rates-%28per-100-000-population%29), [Number of deaths attributed to non-communicable diseases, by type of disease and sex](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/number-of-deaths-attributed-to-non-communicable-diseases-by-type-of-disease-and-sex), [Life expectancy at birth (years)](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/life-expectancy-at-birth-%28years%29), [Healthy life expectancy (HALE) at birth (years)](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/gho-ghe-hale-healthy-life-expectancy-at-birth), [Neonatal mortality rate (per 1000 live births)](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/neonatal-mortality-rate-%28per-1000-live-births%29), [Adult mortality rate (probability of dying between 15 and 60 years per 1000 population)](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/adult-mortality-rate-%28probability-of-dying-between-15-and-60-years-per-1000-population%29), [Healthy life expectancy (HALE) at age 60 (years)](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/gho-ghe-hale-healthy-life-expectancy-at-age-60), [Stillbirth rate (per 1000 total births)](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/stillbirth-rate-%28per-1000-total-births%29), [Life expectancy at age 60 (years)](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/life-expectancy-at-age-60-%28years%29), [Mortality rate among children ages 5 to 9 years (per 1000 children aged 5)](https://www.who.int/data/gho/data/indicators/indicator-details/GHO/mortality-rate-among-children-ages-5-to-9-years-%28per-1000-children-aged-5%29)
